# Frontend Patterns

## Workspace state — always use Zustand

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD
const activeWorkspaceId = useAppStore(s => s.activeWorkspaceId)

// ❌ BAD — don't pass workspaceId as props through component trees
```

## API calls always pass workspaceId

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD
api.graph(activeWorkspaceId)
api.search(query, activeWorkspaceId)
api.deleteFile(path, activeWorkspaceId)

// ❌ BAD
api.graph()
```

## Electron IPC bridge — never use raw fetch()

All HTTP calls go through `apiGet / post / del` from `api.ts` which routes through
`window.bina.api.*` IPC in Electron. Raw `fetch()` bypasses the bridge and hits CSP
errors (`connect-src` only allows `localhost:8765`, not `127.0.0.1`).

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD
import { apiGet } from '../api'
const data = await apiGet<MyType>('/some/endpoint')

// ❌ BAD — CSP violation in Electron
fetch('http://127.0.0.1:8765/some/endpoint')
```

## D3 canvas graph — pointer events, not mouse events

The `GraphCanvas` uses manual pan/zoom (no `d3-zoom`). Use `onPointerDown/Move/Up`
so events fire before any third-party listeners and the 4px drag threshold works:

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD — 4px threshold prevents micro-movements from swallowing clicks
if (!dragMovedRef.current && Math.sqrt(dx*dx + dy*dy) > 4) {
  dragMovedRef.current = true
}

// ❌ BAD — any mousemove sets moved=true and kills the click
const handleMouseMove = () => { dragMovedRef.current = true }
```

## Stale closure prevention — use refs for callbacks

When a `useCallback(fn, [])` needs to call a prop or piece of state:

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD
const onNodeClickRef = useRef(onNodeClick)
useEffect(() => { onNodeClickRef.current = onNodeClick }, [onNodeClick])
// inside useCallback(fn, []): onNodeClickRef.current(node)

// ❌ BAD — onNodeClick captured at initial render, always stale
const handler = useCallback(() => { onNodeClick(node) }, [])
```

## Graph node deletion — trigger immediate reload

After deleting a file, call `onNodeDeleted()` to reload the graph immediately.
Don't wait for the 5-second status poll.

```typescript
await api.deleteFile(node.path, activeWorkspaceId)
onNodeDeletedRef.current?.()   // triggers loadFullGraph() in MainLayout
```

## GraphNode fields

- `id` = MD5 hash (not path)
- `community_id` = Louvain partition integer → maps to `COMMUNITY_PALETTE`
- `forced` on edges = artificial edge for isolated nodes, render as dotted line
